<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-077-397 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 175 495</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  August 26 1991 v13 n34 p82(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Patents gain favor with software firms: vendors slow to adopt oldweapon. (News Analysis)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Busse, Torsten.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The patenting of computer software is a major trend, withdevelopers filing a record number of patents with the US PatentOffice in 1991.andP;  Apple applies for about 50 patents a year andholds 104; IBM has approximately 9,000 software patents.andP;  Othervendors seek to use patents as weapons for cross-licensingagreements as well as for legal protection.andP;  Microsoft currentlyhas only nine software patents but is considering applications formany more.andP;  Ashton-Tate is considering patenting its technology,something it has never done in the past; Borland International Inchas three patents pending.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software packagesPatentTrendsSoftware Publishers.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Computer patent applications on the rise. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>